8. Write an SQL query to show the second highest salary from a table.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
Ans SELECT MAX(SALARY) AS SECOND_HIGHEST_SALARY \
FROM Worker \
WHERE SALARY < (SELECT MAX(SALARY) FROM Worker);\
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 9.Write an SQL query to fetch the departments that have less than three people in it.\
Ans SELECT DEPARTMENT, COUNT(*) AS WORKER_COUNT \
FROM Worker \
GROUP BY DEPARTMENT \
HAVING COUNT(*) < 3;\
